HEADWORD: Gault
<hw>Gault</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Norw.
<ets>gald</ets> hard ground, Icel. <ets>gald</ets> hard snow.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A series of beds of clay and marl in the South
of England, between the upper and lower greensand of the Cretaceous
period.</def>⟦br⟧
